article.headline: Tenn.-Martin 86, SE Missouri 73
article.story: MARTIN, Tenn. -- Lester Hudson scored 24 points to lead Tennessee-Martin to an 86-73 victory over Southeast Missouri State on Thursday night. Hudson, the nation's second-leading scorer at 27.4 points entering the game, helped the Skyhawks (13-6, 6-3 Ohio Valley Conference) win for the 11th time in 12 games. He also had 11 rebounds and six assists. Kenard Moore, who was 11 of 19 from the field, scored 28 points to lead Southeast Missouri State (3-17, 0-9), which has lost nine consecutive games. Tennessee-Martin went on a 21-7 run in the first half for a 45-29 halftime lead. Southeast Missouri State was 13 of 29 from the free-throw line (44.8 percent). Marquis Weddle and Olajide Hay added 16 points each for Tennessee-Martin. Jaycen Herring added 17 points and Calvin Williams had 11 points and 13 rebounds for the Redhawks.
